    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "Fix startup failure with RLIM_INFINITY fd limits",
    "user": {
      "login": "Sjors",
      "id": 10217,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMjE3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10217?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/Sjors",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "When setting the fd limit to unlimited, the node fails to start:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nulimit -n unlimited\r\nbuild/bin/bitcoind\r\nError: Not enough file descriptors available. -1 available, 160 required.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis was caused by `RaiseFileDescriptorLimit()` (introduced in #2568) casting `limitFD.rlim_cur` to `int`, which for `RLIM_INFINITY` overflows to `-1`. Fix it by changing the function arguments to `uint64_t`, which prevents the narrowing.\r\n\r\nThis PR also expands `test/functional/feature_init.py` to cover this, using `resource.setrlimit`. The check is skipped on environments with a hard limit below infinity (or that don't have the Python [Resource module](https://docs.python.org/3/library/resource.html)).\r\n\r\nmacOS by default has a hard limit of infinity, but on e.g. Ubuntu the default hard limit is 524288.",
